Q: Div output prints out vertically even though the output is horizontal in previous lines A: <ol>
<li>You can just make the second <code>gallery</code> scrollable horizontally to not make it vertically by deleting <code>flex-wrap: wrap</code> or commenting it:</li>
</ol>
<pre class="lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>gallery
        {
            display: flex;
            /*flex-wrap: wrap;*/
            justify-content: flex-start;
            background-color: #5B7A8C;
            background-image: url(&quot;KBHassets/images/KBH/KBHtexture.png&quot;);
        }
</code></pre>
<p>2. And then putting a <code>second</code> id in the second <code>gallery</code> element:</p>
<pre class="lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;gallery id=&quot;second&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;gallery-item&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://localhost/KBHassets/sub-pages/a.html&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;KBHassets/images/community/a.png&quot; alt=&quot;a&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;200&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
                    &lt;div class=&quot;desc&quot;&gt;title_a&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;gallery-item&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;http://localhost/KBHassets/sub-pages/b.html&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;KBHassets/images/community/b.png&quot; alt=&quot;b&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;200&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
